q21.value:
The criteria used to reject the fit of models that test measurement invariance are:

Configural:
- significant chi-square test (alpha = .05);
- at least one alternative fit measure (RMSEA, CFI) above these cut-off values (RMSEA &gt; .08, CFI &lt; .95)

Metric:
- significant chi-square test (alpha = .05);
- At least one difference in alternative fit measures (RMSEA, CFI) between the configural and the metric step above these cut-off values (ΔRMSEA &gt; 0.03, ΔCFI &gt; 0.02)

Scalar:
- significant chi-square test (alpha = .05);
- At least one difference in alternative fit measures (RMSEA, CFI) between the metric and scalar step above these cut-off values (ΔRMSEA &gt; 0.01, ΔCFI &gt; 0.01)

